{
  "doc_id": "11563",
  "text": "But in the daily, clinical diagnostic work-up, formalin fixed, paraffinembedded (FFPE) tissue is the primary source, and fresh-frozen material is not routinely collected. Therefore, IHC algorithms have been developed as substitutes and applied with varying concordance to GEP. The most commonly used classification is the Hans algorithm 11 based on the IHC staining results of three proteins: CD10, BCL6 and MUM1, although other systems have also been proposed. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] However, these IHC algorithms will only identify two groups; GCB or non-GCB, since they cannot identify cases classified as UC by GEP.",
